   resources at the edge of the network. Fog supplies processing, data,
   storing, and application amenities to ultimate operators. The management
   strategies have a great impact on fog computing, such as monitoring and
   optimizing, the correlated components for improving the performance,
   availability, security, and any fundamental operational requirement.
   However, as far as we know, no organized study exists about analyzing
   their importance in fog environments. This paper provides a detailed
   survey for covering the current state-of-the-art in fog management. This
